main event: On November 6, 1957, an unidentified flying object was sighted over Kaisong, Korea, observed by military personnel including 19 individuals who reported a brilliant flash of light and a luminous object.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 minutes and described as spherical, metallic, and emitting bright lights.,Witnesses reported no sound or exhaust from the object.,The phenomenon was initially categorized as 'Insufficient Information' without definitive identification.,Multiple military observers confirmed the sighting, enhancing its credibility.,Radar contact was also established, indicating the object was not an aircraft or known celestial body.
witness description: Military personnel from the 1st Army Corps stationed in the demilitarized zone.
